\.TH man 1 "10 November 2019" "0.1" "Simple-shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- Linux shell program recreation that will provide the user with a user interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
$ COMMAND [-FLAGS]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Simple-shell will take the commands from the keyboard and based on that imput it gathers it and execute programs, just afetr it finishes executeng it will display that command output followed with the new prompt.
.SH Compiling
gcc -Wall -Wextra -Werror -pedantic *.c
.SH OPTION
Built-ins
.br
	env
- It will display the current environment
.br
	exit
- It will exit from the mini-shell.
.SH EXAMPLES
$ ls
.br
Display the list of files in the current dir
.br


$ /bin/pwd
.br
Displays display the current directory address
.br

$ exit or Ctrl + D
.br
Exits from the shell.
.SH ENVIRONMENT

Examples of Environment Variables

     PATH
               A set of directories where executable files are located

     PWD
               The current directory address
.SH SEE ALSO
.I sh(1), execve(2), signal(2), exit(2), isatty(3).
.SH Bugs
No known bugs
